        "text": "<@U060RULT44D>: part of the reason it's done this way is to make e-mail commands work. For example, you can write a message to <mailto:r-devel-request@r-project.org|r-devel-request@r-project.org> saying\nset authenticate YOUR_WEAK_PASSWORD\nset reminders off\n\nand it won't be reminding you any more. \"set delivery off\" could also be useful if you don't want to read a list for a while. This is what sets the upper bound for security.",
